  "text": "• Different coloring of nodes may help reveal additional patterns in data (see images in supplemental material). For example, ozone fluctuates according to the season period. During the spring-summer, ozone levels are higher due to variations in sunlight and UV radiation [CITATION_1] . In addition, concentration of carbon monoxide, nitrogen, ozone, sulfur dioxide, and particulate matter decreases gradually over the years, reaching stability in 2010. This finding is associated with an improvement of air-quality [CITATION_2] .",
